docs.lead_paragraph: Herrera Says Aim Is to Lift Group's Influence in World by Joint Trade Policy WASHINGTON, June 22-- Felipe Herrera, President of the Inter-American Development Bank, proposed today a fullfledged Latin American common market that would go far beyond the present free-trade area and include all the Latin American countries. Mr. Herrera provided the terms of his proposal in detail.
